By Onyekachukwu Obi Reverend Father Jude Oniah has admonished Christians to be grateful for what they have and imbibe the spirit of submissiveness, as Catholics all over the world commemorate Palm Sunday. The clergyman, who delivered his Sunday homily at the Parish Priest of Our Lady Queen of Peace Catholic Parish Utako, Abuja, said the event is observed Sunday before Easter to mark the beginning of the Holy Week. “You should be grateful for what you have which is the requirement that ushered in more.” the parish priest said. He advised the congregants to be courageous and use the season to reconcile with God and live a life of salvation.